.TH "gmap_protect_rmap" 9 "gmap_protect_rmap" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gmap_protect_rmap \- restrict access rights to memory (RO) and create an rmap
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gmap_protect_rmap
.BI "(struct gmap *sg "  ","
.BI "unsigned long raddr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long paddr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sg" 12
pointer to the shadow guest address space structure
.IP "raddr" 12
rmap address in the shadow gmap
.IP "paddr" 12
address in the parent guest address space
.IP "len" 12
length of the memory area to protect
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 if successfully protected and the rmap was created, -ENOMEM
if out of memory and -EFAULT if paddr is invalid.
